	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi, I'm Neige, the guy who asked questions about how dark race rogues got jipped in deceptive equipment such as mask of deceptions. I play a monk as a main character, so I'll answer your question.<br><br>A Monk does not need a weapon when fighting; it IS a weapon. The monk cultivates every aspect of his body to turn it into a deadly machine of destruction. He can control his cellular reconstruction with the mend technique, and slow his breathing to nothing with the Feign Death skill.<br><br>The reason why Rogues cannot Feign Death are IC purely. You rogues do not posess the perfect body control to slow your vital system to appear dead. A Rogue is not a monk, it's a warrior, with a whole lot of sneakiness.<br><br>That's how I'm RPing my little rogue nowadays. He tells everyone he meets that he is a learned warrior of the TierDal, using strategic fencing techniques to create critical hits (a.k.a backstabs). He knows that if he would appear in broad daylight, a flock of adoring fans would mob him for an autograph, so that's why he stays hidden. He doesn't pickpocket the monsters, he just gives himself his due pay if the group does not appreciate his talent correctly. In other words, BS does not just mean BackStab when refering to my rogue.<br><br>But Rogues will never have Feign Death. You already have super invisibility. That's good enough for you.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
