	   <tr><td colspan=2>I will concede, you have described monks very well, but having a lvl 40 Rogue as my main, I <br>beg to differ with your description of Rogues.<br><br>A rogue is not a warrior in my opinion, we do not get to wear super-ac items and we do not get criticals in frontal battle.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our hps are far less<br>than a warriors, simply put, we are not tanks, we<br>are secondary-tanks.  We are that which fills the void between Warriors and Pure Casters when it comes to a mob having something to bash on.<br><br>With some of the weapons that are available for warriors, their regular hits either match or exceed a rogue's backstab.  This means that Rogues are a disadvantaged class based on the <br>norm of a warrior being baseline for melee classes.<br><br>I agree with the prior poster that we are the masters of deception.  Feigning Death is a deception, but I do not care about getting the skill, all it means is that we have to think about our attack method.<br><br>This is not a complaint regarding Rogues and not a whine regarding Warriors.  What this note should be considered, is gentle correction to the conception that rogues are warriors.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
